# Predictive Maintenance ML Project

## Objective
This project predicts machine failures and identifies their root causes using machine condition data.  
It is tied to my **Production & Industrial Engineering coursework**, focusing on reliability, quality control, and process optimization.

## Methodology
- Dataset: AI4I Predictive Maintenance dataset
- Features: Air temperature, Process temperature, Rotational speed, Torque, Tool wear
- Models: Random Forest Classifier
- Steps:
  1. Binary failure prediction
  2. Failure type classification (TWF, HDF, PWF, OSF, RNF)
  3. Feature importance analysis
  4. Visualization (heatmap of features vs. failure types)

## Results
- Tool wear is the dominant driver of Tool Wear Failures (TWF).
- Process temperature strongly influences Heat Dissipation Failures (HDF).
- Torque and speed anomalies cause Power Failures (PWF).
- Torque spikes lead to Overstrain Failures (OSF).
- Random Failures (RNF) show no clear driver.

## Tech Stack
- Python (pandas, scikit-learn, seaborn, matplotlib)
- Jupyter Notebook

